        <title type="text">Questions posted on beta are not visible in feeds on main site. How should I watch my tag of interest at one place?</title>
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="discussion" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="questions" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="tag-watching" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="redesign-2026" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="open-ended-questions" />
        <author>
            <name>Amit Joshi</name>
            <uri>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/users/5779732</uri>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/438331/questions-posted-on-beta-are-not-visible-in-feeds-on-main-site-how-should-i-wat" />
        <published>2026-02-26T13:43:58Z</published>
        <updated>2026-02-27T07:41:07Z</updated>
        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I recently observed that one of my Custom Filters was showing blue circle, indicating that there is new question or activity in the tag I am watching. I clicked on it to see the activity, but there was none. This happened again. Just being curious, I went to beta site; and found a new question in the tag I am following. But, this question is not visible on main site. It is not visible in Feeds. It is not visible even if I search with the said tag.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I then went back to beta and posted an answer there (or should I say &amp;quot;I &#x27;discussed&#x27; there&amp;quot;?). The answer I posted (on beta) is visible in my Profile under Answers tab; thanks. When I click on the answer, I can see the complete Q/A on main site; that&#x27;s a relief because I can use all the features on main site.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;As the questions posted on beta are not visible on main site Feeds, it is hard for the user to watch the tags they are interested in. It is not productive for any user to watch two sites to participate and contribute in the tags they are watching.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Even though, beta is with limited features, data must be common and consistent. Question and Answer is core of the data on Stack Overflow and it must be visible on both the sites immediately.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Without that, how should I watch my tag of interest at one place?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The question: &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/q/79896826&quot;&gt;In HL7 V2.5.1 Original Mode Acknowledgement, what is the meaning of each Acknowledgement Status Code?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This tag is not visible if you search on main:&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/hl7&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/hl7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
        </summary>
    </entry>
