    <entry>
        <id>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/q/438318</id>
        <re:rank scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com">2</re:rank>
        <title type="text">Beta &quot;Newest Questions&quot; page: subjective reactions</title>
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="discussion" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="redesign-2026" />
        <author>
            <name>dbc</name>
            <uri>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/users/3744182</uri>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/438318/beta-newest-questions-page-subjective-reactions" />
        <published>2026-02-25T22:27:55Z</published>
        <updated>2026-02-25T22:27:55Z</updated>
        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I just tried the Beta version of the &amp;quot;Questions&amp;quot; page, and have a few subjective reactions:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Having quick links to other communities is a good thing.  However it&#x27;s my impression that most question that get closed as &amp;quot;off topic&amp;quot; for belonging elsewhere on the network actually should have been asked at Super User -- so I&#x27;d add a link to that community.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;I notice you have removed our current reputation from the header line.  I miss it that because it served as a cue as to whether I was logged in to that specific network site or not.  Additionally, it had a somewhat hidden use related to keyboard navigation.  Specifically, it afforded a fairly quick, backdoor way to access out inboxes via keyboard navigation:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Type the first few characters of the score, with &lt;a href=&quot;https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/search-contents-current-page-text-or-links?redirectslug=Searching&#x2B;within&#x2B;a&#x2B;page&amp;amp;redirectlocale=en-US#w_find-automatically-while-typing-on-a-page&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Search for text when you start typing&amp;quot;&lt;/a&gt; enabled (in Firefox).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Hit &amp;quot;escape&amp;quot; to cancel searching.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Tab to the inbox.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you&#x27;re going to remove this trick please introduce some other way to quickly access the inbox via keyboard navigation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;I can&#x27;t even hazard a guess as to what that &lt;a href=&quot;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/5/5e/Qbert.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;Q*bert-looking&lt;/a&gt; icon in the upper right is supposed to mean:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/LhXU3e4d.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/LhXU3e4d.png&quot; alt=&quot;Q*bert-looking icon&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Even after clicking on it I &lt;strong&gt;still&lt;/strong&gt; can&#x27;t guess.  Maybe you need to give the drop-down menu a title, or implement a tooltip.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;
        </summary>
    </entry>
