        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I just tried the Beta version of the &amp;quot;Questions&amp;quot; page, and have noticed what seems to be a fairly straightforward bug with how the list of questions is presented: the alignment of questions in the &amp;quot;Newest Questions&amp;quot; panel is completely broken.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I would expect the title and text of the questions to be vertically aligned on their left border, but they are not, they are all inconsistently positioned.  This leaves the panel &lt;strong&gt;very&lt;/strong&gt; visually noisy and hard to parse.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Below is a screen shot; I would expect the left edges of the questions to be vertically aligned where I drew the red line, as they are in the current &amp;quot;Questions&amp;quot; page:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/TMHSrXmJ.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/TMHSrXmJ.png&quot; alt=&quot;Screen shot showing poor alignment&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
