        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I just tried the Beta version of the &amp;quot;Questions&amp;quot; page, and have noticed a fairly straightforward bug with keyboard navigation and scrolling.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I use keyboard navigation a lot, but the up arrow, down arrow, page up and page down keys are initially broken -- I can&#x27;t use them to scroll down in the list of questions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I &lt;em&gt;think&lt;/em&gt; the problem here is that you have two separate scrolling panels -- the question panel and that other panel thing on the left.  Because I need to use large fonts, the other panel also gets a scrollbar, and so Firefox doesn&#x27;t know which one to scroll.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Please don&#x27;t break such basic keyboard navigation features. For those of us who have multiple accessibility issues it&#x27;s important for them to work in a standard way.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/TMHSrXmJ.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/TMHSrXmJ.png&quot; alt=&quot;Screen shot&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
