        <title type="text">If you&#x27;re going to force the Stacks Editor on your users, can it finally have parity with the old editor?</title>
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="bug" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="feature-request" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="status-review" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="stacks-editor" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="redesign-2026" />
        <author>
            <name>Thom A</name>
            <uri>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/users/2029983</uri>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/438283/if-youre-going-to-force-the-stacks-editor-on-your-users-can-it-finally-have-pa" />
        <published>2026-02-25T09:09:50Z</published>
        <updated>2026-02-26T19:48:48Z</updated>
        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;It seems that on the Beta site, when you are answering a question, you have the choice of the Stacks Editor, sans Markdown with Preview Mode, or... Oh, that&#x27;s the end of the list. This is a TERRIBLE decision.&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/zQKctA5n.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/zQKctA5n.png&quot; alt=&quot;Image of the Stacks Editor with a freehand red arrow pointing at where the &amp;quot;Markdown with Preview Mode&amp;quot; should be shown and badly written freehand red text stating &amp;quot;Markdown w/ preview where?&amp;quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The Stacks Editor has been feature lacking, and buggy, for &lt;em&gt;years&lt;/em&gt; and those bugs have no sign of being fixed. Why, therefore, are you forcing users to use this buggy editor in your new site? Why is it still so feature lacking?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Even when the Stacks Editor does have the Markdown with Preview Mode, when asking a question, it&#x27;s not even rendering correctly:&lt;br /&gt;&#xA;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/YjaOm22x.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/YjaOm22x.png&quot; alt=&quot;Image showing that the italics and bold markdown, and underline markup aren&#x27;t rendered&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Worse, if I switch to Rich Text and back the ancient bug of escaping the HTML is &lt;em&gt;still&lt;/em&gt; there: &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;u&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; becomes &lt;code&gt;\&amp;lt;u\&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Even worserer* is that the Stacks Editor &lt;em&gt;defaults&lt;/em&gt; to Rich Text (which is the worst mode in my opinion) by default. If you change the mode and refresh you are back in Rich Text mode, meaning that it will quite happily break your content. Is that truly &amp;quot;by design&amp;quot;?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The beta site needs a way to use the old, feature rich, working editor. You, Stack Inc, needs to put some &lt;em&gt;serious&lt;/em&gt; time into actually getting the Stacks Editor to work; it&#x27;s still a broken mess and is not appropriate for release (without an opt out option).&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
        </summary>
    </entry>
