        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;The new button on mobile is incredibly large and is taking up a most of the the top bar. This, especially as a mod who has extra buttons, is actually really annoying, there are now only &lt;em&gt;four&lt;/em&gt; buttons visible. Prior to the button being added, and the change to the logo, it used to be eight.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/BB2lWczu.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/BB2lWczu.png&quot; alt=&quot;image of top bar on Stack Overflow&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/X9zD2cgW.jpg&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/X9zD2cgW.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Image of the top bar on Stack Overflow prior to today&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This means that when I load a page, I can&#x27;t even see how many unread items I have in my inbox (I have 2 at the moment for reference):&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/OKxFJK18.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.sstatic.net/OKxFJK18.png&quot; alt=&quot;Image of top bar again, showing the inbox isn&#x27;t visible by default&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;How can I hide the button, or at least put it somewhere that doesn&#x27;t have a significant impact on the use of the site?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For reference, I am opted out of experiments (something I would say the Beta is), yet it&#x27;s still visible.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
