        <id>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/q/438259</id>
        <re:rank scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com">159</re:rank>
        <title type="text">Is the new Stack Overflow beta UX really useful? What is the purpose of these changes?</title>
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="discussion" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="design" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="comments" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="user-experience" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="redesign-2026" />
        <author>
            <name>chqrlie</name>
            <uri>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/users/4593267</uri>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/438259/is-the-new-stack-overflow-beta-ux-really-useful-what-is-the-purpose-of-these-ch" />
        <published>2026-02-24T21:12:53Z</published>
        <updated>2026-02-26T20:39:56Z</updated>
        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I just tried &lt;a href=&quot;https://beta.stackoverflow.com&quot;&gt;the Stack Overflow beta&lt;/a&gt;. This new UX has some obvious and less obvious changes. Here is a tentative list with my personal feedback:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; less color&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; no visible separation for the top banner&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; no score info for the OP or the contributors: requires a click on the avatar icon&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; different icons for shortcuts to inbox and achievements&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E; no margins&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; question info appears above title: author, time, tags... this info is not as useful as the question score.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; question score is smaller and hidden below the question&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; no access to the count of up and down votes&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;the question timeline is hiding in a new place: behind the &lt;em&gt;asked xxx days ago&lt;/em&gt; link&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;bold font for the question title (why not, but more vertical space wasted)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; there is no option to bookmark/save the post and any of its answers&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; answer author is above answer but score is below, same as for the question, but this creates confusion as answers are not clearly separated from each other.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E;&#x1F44E; larger font for comments, no clear separation between answers.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Is this last point a design choice? It makes comments much more prominent to the point where they occupy more vertical space than answers. They are actually indistinguishable from answers. Comments are not more important than answers, they are the place where people make suggestions regarding answers so they can be improved. Threading was already a step in the wrong direction, wasting vertical space for little value, but promoting the font size makes things even worse and blurring answers and comments in a single flow of text creates confusion for readers and defeats the purpose.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What problem are these changes trying to solve?&lt;/strong&gt; The site is less and less appealing to contributors, and many seem to leave... I&#x27;m afraid this is only going to fuel this trend.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
        </summary>
    </entry>
