        <title type="text">Beta claims sharing links are copied to clipboard even if they aren&#x27;t</title>
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="bug" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="status-declined" />
            <category scheme="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/tags" term="redesign-2026" />
        <author>
            <name>Karl Knechtel</name>
            <uri>https://meta.stackoverflow.com/users/523612</uri>
        </author>
        <link rel="alternate" href="https://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/438258/beta-claims-sharing-links-are-copied-to-clipboard-even-if-they-arent" />
        <published>2026-02-24T20:43:18Z</published>
        <updated>2026-02-25T17:18:39Z</updated>
        <summary type="html">
            &lt;p&gt;I have my browser configured (intentionally) in such a way that JavaScript to copy onto the clipboard does not work. When I try to use the &amp;quot;copy&amp;quot; buttons on source code (in either the main site or beta), nothing is actually copied, as I&#x27;d expect. Similarly for &amp;quot;Copy link&amp;quot; in the main site &amp;quot;Share&amp;quot; interface, and the &amp;quot;Share&amp;quot; links below answers and comments in the beta.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;However, on the main site the error is at least detected in the &amp;quot;Share&amp;quot; interface. I get a red banner at the top of the window reading &amp;quot;Could not copy link to clipboard.&amp;quot;. But in the beta, I am incorrectly told &amp;quot;Link copied to clipboard&amp;quot; with a check-mark icon in a green banner.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;
        </summary>
    </entry>
